{"word":"G684 - ἀπώλεια - apṓleia - ap-o'-li-a - Damnable","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>மூல வார்த்தை / Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">ἀπώλεια</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>எழுத்துமாற்றம் / Transliteration: </strong>apṓleia"},{"paragraph":"<strong>ஒலிபெயர்ப்பு / Phonetic: </strong>ap-o'-li-a"},{"paragraph":"<strong>சுருக்க விளக்கம் / Short Definition: </strong>Damnable"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"அழிவு, கேடு, நாசம், மரணம், வீண் - பெண்பால் பெயர்ச்சொல்"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"1. a destroying, utter destruction"},{"paragraph":"2. a perishing, ruin, destruction"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"parts-of-speech\"><strong>Part(s) of speech:</strong> Noun Feminine / பெயர்ச்சொல் (பெண்பால்)</span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"original-in-english\"><strong>ஆங்கில மூலம் / Original in English:</strong> From a presumed derivative of <a href=\"#/G622 - ἀπόλλυμι - apóllymi - ap-ol'-loo-mee/622\">G622</a>; <i>ruin</i> or <i>loss</i> (physical, spiritual or eternal): - damnable (-nation), destruction, die, perdition, X perish, pernicious ways, waste."},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G622 - ἀπόλλυμι - apóllymi - ap-ol'-loo-mee/622\">G622</a>, <a href=\"#/G623 - Ἀπολλύων - Apollýōn - ap-ol-loo'-ohn/623\">G623</a>, <a href=\"#/G684 - ἀπώλεια - apṓleia - ap-o'-li-a/684\">G684</a>"}]}